    "accordion_section_LXcTpy": {
      "type": "accordion-section",
      "blocks": {
        "item_cBMGT4": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is Collagen?",
            "content": "<p>Collagen is the most plentiful - and often considered one of the most essential - proteins in the human body. It serves as a key structural component of tissues such as skin, hair, nails, joints, and bones, contributing to strength, elasticity, and flexibility. As the body’s natural collagen production decreases with age, supplementing collagen through your diet can help support and maintain healthy collagen levels over time.</p>",
            "open_by_default": true
          }
        },
        "item_Jy86pY": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What are the signs of collagen deficiency?",
            "content": "<p>When your body lacks collagen, noticeable changes begin to appear. Your skin may become dry, lose firmness, and develop wrinkles. Hair can become weak, dull, and prone to breakage, while nails may turn fragile and easily crack. In addition, low collagen levels can affect your joints, causing stiffness or discomfort and increasing the risk of joint issues over time. That’s why daily collagen supplementation is essential to help maintain beauty and overall health from within.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "item_m6crw9": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Why is it necessary to take collagen daily?",
            "content": "<p>Collagen levels begin to decline after the age of 25, decreasing by about 1–1.5% each year. From the age of 35 onward, this loss accelerates, and without proper supplementation, the body starts to age more rapidly, leading to wrinkles, dry skin, and loss of firmness. Therefore, taking collagen daily is essential to help replenish what’s lost, maintain youthful skin, and support overall beauty from within.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "item_Xd6RzC": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Where does the Collagen 82X come from?",
            "content": "<p>The 82X Collagen (500ml) contains 120,000mg of collagen peptides extracted from deep-sea fish. It is also enriched with a blend of 82 naturally fermented plant extracts that are packed with essential nutrients like minerals, vitamins, amino acids, and flavonoids. These ingredients help support overall health.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "item_jhq4AQ": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Does it really work?",
            "content": "<p>More than 10,000 customers have been satisfied with the product. Daily collagen intake helps hydrate the skin, reduce wrinkles, and improve digestive health, while also supporting a healthier, slimmer body when combined with a balanced diet, healthy lifestyle, and regular exercise.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
